FBIS3-27687 "drchi039_a_94011" FBIS-CHI-94-039 Document Type:Daily Report 28 February 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS General India Opposes Introduction of Discriminatory NPT Regime BK2502165294 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 GMT 25 Feb 94 BK2502165294 Delhi All India Radio Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] India has rejected a backdoor introduction of the discriminatory Nuclear Nonproliferation Treaty, NPT, regime. Indian experts told a workshop on nuclear disarmament at Shanghai in China that India firmly opposes any move to introduce discriminatory regime in the circulation of material needed for nuclear fission. Experts from India, China, the United States, and Pakistan are attending the workshop.
